OL,3,CEx-England cricketer's daughter would
OL,4,Chave survived with quicker care `
OL,5,Ccoroner
OL,7,F"The cognitive bias towards resus
OL,8,Fpatients would have been directed in
OL,9,FBethan's favour at the time of her
OL,10,Farrival rather than once the lactate
OL,11,Fresult was available.
OL,13,F"On balance I find that had this
OL,14,Fdirect admission to resus and prompter
OL,15,Frecognition and treatment occurred,
OL,16,Fthen cardiac arrest would not have
OL,17,Foccurred when it did, which would have
OL,18,Fenabled more time for other
OL,19,Fspecialities to become involved in
OL,20,FBethan's care.
